TY  - JOUR
TI  - The Continuous Representation of a Social Preference Ordering
AU  - Kelly, J. S.
AB  - [It is shown that single-peaked, continuous utility functions do not, in general,aggregate in majority voting to a continuous social utility function. Conditions on individual preference orderings to guarantee a continuous social utility function are presented for a simple case.]
